Binary Tree Traversal Example
This repository contains a simple Python script (sort.py) demonstrating the fundamental concepts of binary tree data structures and their various traversal methods: Preorder, Inorder, and Postorder. This code is designed for educational purposes to illustrate how nodes in a tree can be visited in different sequences.

